text.__SUMMARY__: Shorea symingtonii (also called White Meranti) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family. It is endemic to Sabah, Malaysia.
text.Sources: Ashton, P. (1998). "Shorea symingtonii". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 1998: e.T31930A9669561. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T31930A9669561.en. Retrieved 15 January 2018.
